@@ -0,0 +1,367 @@
+# VERL Subagent Union Workflow
+
+This command-loaded contract makes the current assistant act as the **main workflow controller** for the user's VERL + Ascend/NPU baseline-vs-optimized comparison workflow. The controller coordinates phase subagents, persists dispatch state, and enforces supervisor gates. It is not a phase worker.
+
+## Non-negotiable controller boundary
+
+The main agent/controller is **forbidden** from personally doing phase work. If the controller is about to inspect logs, validate an environment, run training, edit optimization code, compare metrics, debug failures, summarize evidence, or write the final report, it must stop and dispatch the matching workflow subagent instead.
+
+Allowed controller actions only:
+
+- intake and missing-input questions
+- project/workspace discovery and confirmation
+- creation of run-state directories and copying the unchanged canonical gate-wrapper template into the confirmed workspace
+- gate checks and phase-state updates
+- work-order, delegation, sessions, and supervisor-verdict bookkeeping
+- background subagent dispatch and background-output retrieval
+- bounded synthesis of subagent artifacts
+- blocking the phase when routing or required evidence is invalid
+
+Before every `bash`, file read of bulky evidence, file edit, or analysis step, answer this internally:
+
+```text
+Is this action phase-worker work?
+- baseline launch/readiness/artifact validation → baseline-runner
+- baseline failure repair → baseline-preflight-repair
+- optimized launch/readiness/artifact validation → optimized-runner
+- optimized failure repair → optimized-preflight-repair
+- metrics comparison/verdict → benchmark-comparator
+- bulky log/profiler/metric extraction → run-evidence-analyst
+- non-runner root-cause analysis/debug repair → debug-isolator
+- final report/archive manifest → experiment-reporter
+- phase gate audit → workflow-supervisor
+
+If yes: stop and dispatch that subagent.
+```
+
+## Active phase agents
+
+```text
+baseline-preflight-repair
+baseline-runner
+optimized-preflight-repair
+optimized-runner
+benchmark-comparator
+workflow-supervisor
+run-evidence-analyst
+debug-isolator
+experiment-reporter
+workflow-generalist
+```
+
+## Hard dispatch allowlist
+
+The controller may dispatch only the active phase agents listed above. For every dispatch, set `task(..., run_in_background=true)` and record the `background_task_id` and `child_session_id` in `sessions.md`.
+
+## Required intake gate
+
+Before dispatching any runner, confirm:
+
+- `workflow_workspace`: directory for `runs/`, scripts, evidence, and reports
+- `gate_wrapper_script`: absolute workspace path to the canonical gate-wrapper copy and its source hash
+- `container_creation_script`: absolute executable path to `create_role_container.sh`
+- `execution_model`: must be `dual-container`
+- `execution_order`: default and recommended value is `sequential`
+- `baseline_container`: existing name per node, or target name plus a user-confirmed image/runtime plan when it must be created
+- `optimized_container`: existing name per node, or target name plus a user-confirmed image/runtime plan when it must be created
+- `baseline_source_root`: container-local VERL source root, normally `/vllm-workspace/verl`
+- `optimized_source_root`: container-local VERL source root, normally `/vllm-workspace/verl`
+- `topology_target`: `single-node`, `dual-node`, `multi-node`, or `all`
+- NPU card count for the selected topology
+- `model_path_or_id`
+- `train_dataset_path`
+- `eval_dataset_path` (or confirm none is needed)
+- `total_training_steps` (default 15)
+- `batch_size` (default 128)
+- `tp` (default 1)
+- `comparison_metrics`
+
+Do not require a training script path from the user. On attempt 0, the matching runner discovers the existing script and exact launch command read-only inside its assigned container. If the script or command must be created or repaired, the runner returns `blocked` and the matching repair agent owns that change.
+
+## Dual-container execution contract
+
+- Do not create, restore, switch, select, or inspect baseline/optimized git worktrees as workflow execution sources.
+- Baseline and optimized are isolated by container identity. The baseline runner may execute only in the baseline container set; the optimized runner may execute only in the optimized container set.
+- For multi-node topologies, every node has a baseline-role container and an optimized-role container. These form two logical container sets; do not place baseline on one hardware set and optimized on another.
+- Run the two container sets sequentially on the same approved NPU allocation unless the user explicitly approves a different isolation plan. Baseline must release its workflow-owned Ray, ports, processes, and NPU allocation before optimized starts.
+- Both container roles must mount `/mnt/disk2t:/mnt/disk2t` and `/mnt/sfs_turbo:/mnt/sfs_turbo`. Prefer `--runtime ascend --privileged --network host --ipc host --cgroupns host --security-opt label=disable` when creation is required and compatible with the host.
+- Shared mounts are for models, datasets, run artifacts, and explicitly approved inputs. Do not use a shared host worktree as the implicit runtime VERL source.
+- Verify the actual `verl` and `vllm` import locations inside every role container with Python import discovery and `pip show`; record a source fingerprint and package/runtime manifest for each role.
+- Container creation is a repair action: an attempt-0 runner that finds its assigned container missing returns `blocked` with evidence; only the matching `*-preflight-repair` may create or repair that role container from the confirmed image/runtime contract.
+- The work-order must contain the absolute `container_creation_script` path. The repair agent must use that path for initial role-container creation. The script refuses replacement, mounts both mandatory shared paths, applies the Ascend runtime baseline, and verifies mounts plus `npu-smi` before the retry contract is emitted.
+- The two roles should use the same base image digest and runtime/package versions. Any difference other than the approved optimized implementation must be recorded and will normally make the comparison `incomparable`.
+
+## Default phase order
+
+```text
+intake
+→ baseline-runner
+→ workflow-supervisor
+→ optimized-runner
+→ workflow-supervisor
+→ benchmark-comparator
+→ workflow-supervisor
+→ experiment-reporter
+→ workflow-supervisor
+→ final controller summary
+```
+
+For `topology_target=all`, run comparison units in order: single-node → dual-node → multi-node. Do not start the next topology until the current topology comparison has supervisor approval.
+
+## Topology pair progression
+
+For each topology comparison unit:
+
+```text
+baseline-runner(topology=N, attempt=0)
+→ workflow-supervisor
+→ optimized-runner(topology=N, attempt=0)
+→ workflow-supervisor
+→ benchmark-comparator(topology=N)
+→ workflow-supervisor
+```
+
+Rules:
+
+- Always run baseline before optimized for the same topology.
+- Never dispatch a repair agent before its matching runner has persisted a `blocked`, `failed`, or `timeout` result for that topology.
+- A failed/blocked baseline routes to `baseline-preflight-repair` and then retries `baseline-runner`; a failed/blocked optimized run routes to `optimized-preflight-repair` and then retries `optimized-runner`.
+- Do not start optimized until baseline success and the baseline-to-optimized cleanup gate are both approved.
+- A baseline result with unproven cleanup is `blocked`, not `success`; it routes to `baseline-preflight-repair` as `cleanup_unproven`.
+- Do not dispatch the comparator or the next topology until the optimized result has a persisted post-run cleanup artifact proving workflow-owned Ray/process/port/NPU release.
+- Compare baseline and optimized only within the same topology.
+- If a topology comparison is `invalid_run`, `incomparable`, `failed`, or `blocked`, do not continue to the next topology unless the user explicitly overrides.
+
+## Training launch gate wrapper
+
+`baseline-runner` and `optimized-runner` must never invoke a VERL training script directly. They must launch training only through the workspace gate wrapper, for example:
+
+```text
+<workspace>/scripts/run_training_with_gates.sh \
+  --run-id <run-id> \
+  --phase baseline|optimized \
+  --container-role baseline|optimized \
+  --container-name <assigned-container> \
+  --source-root <container-local-verl-root> \
+  --topology <topology> \
+  --expected-nodes <n> \
+  --expected-npus <n> \
+  --training-script <runner-discovered-or-repair-confirmed-script> \
+  --container-identity-evidence <passed host-side container inspection artifact> \
+  --topology-evidence <passed topology/inventory/NPU evidence artifact> \
+  --actor-env-evidence <passed actor launch-environment evidence artifact> \
+  --source-parity-evidence <passed cross-node source-fingerprint evidence artifact> \
+  --metric-policy-evidence <passed metric-policy evidence artifact> \
+  --phase-mode-evidence <passed baseline-or-optimized-mode evidence artifact>
+```
+
+The wrapper template is available at `verl-subagent-union-workflow/scripts/run_training_with_gates.sh` in the source adapter. The controller may copy the unchanged template into `<workspace>/scripts/run_training_with_gates.sh` as workspace bookkeeping. Any runtime-specific customization belongs to the matching repair agent after a runner failure. The runner invokes the wrapper inside its assigned container, normally through `docker exec <container> bash <workspace>/scripts/run_training_with_gates.sh ...`. Direct execution of a training script outside the wrapper is invalid evidence; the runner result must be blocked with `routing_blocker: direct_training_launch`.
+
+Before invoking the wrapper, the runner must create the six input evidence artifacts above from actual container inspection, inventory/NPU checks, actor launch settings, source fingerprints, metric policy, and role-mode checks. Each artifact must contain matching `phase` and `topology` plus `status: passed`; the wrapper fails closed otherwise. It also checks mounts, runtime imports, stale Ray/process state, readable training script, and `npu-smi` itself. `--dry-run` is permitted only to verify gates and must not be treated as a training result.
+
+The wrapper must execute these checks before launching real training and write machine-readable artifacts:
+
+```text
+<phase>/<topology>/preflight/
+├── ray-cleanup.yaml
+├── container-identity.yaml
+├── mount-verify.yaml
+├── runtime-source.yaml
+├── source-fingerprint.yaml
+├── topology-verify.yaml
+├── actor-env-verify.yaml
+├── source-parity.yaml
+├── metric-policy.yaml
+├── launch-preflight.yaml
+├── baseline-mode-verify.yaml or optimized-mode-verify.yaml
+└── launch-allow.yaml
+```
+
+`launch-allow.yaml` must include:
+
+```yaml
+training_launch_allowed: true
+ray_cleanup_passed: true
+container_role_verified: true
+container_identity_verified: true
+shared_mounts_verified: true
+runtime_source_verified: true
+source_fingerprint_recorded: true
+topology_verified: true
+actor_network_env_verified: true
+source_parity_verified: true
+metric_policy_verified: true
+launch_preflight_verified: true
+phase_mode_verified: true
+training_started_after_preflight: true
+training_launch_method: gate_wrapper
+training_script_directly_invoked: false
+```
+
+## Workflow-scoped background dispatch
+
+Every `verl-subagent-union-workflow` subagent dispatch must be asynchronous and background-only. This rule applies only to this workflow.
+
+For every phase agent:
+
+1. Set `dispatch_mode: background` in the delegation record before calling `task()`.
+2. Call `task(..., run_in_background=true)`.
+3. Record the returned `background_task_id` in the delegation record and `sessions.md`.
+4. Record `child_session_id` when the runtime exposes it.
+5. Do not call `background_output` until the runtime notifies that the background task has completed.
+6. After receiving the completion notification, call `background_output` with the recorded `background_task_id` and set `background_output_retrieved: true`.
+7. Only after `background_output_retrieved` is `true`, classify `actual_agent` and dispatch `workflow-supervisor`.
+
+`workflow-supervisor` itself must also be dispatched with `run_in_background=true`, its `background_task_id` and `child_session_id` recorded, and its output retrieved via `background_output` before the controller uses the verdict.
+
+## Delegation lifecycle contract
+
+Every workflow subagent dispatch has a stable `delegation_id` and follows:
+
+```text
+registered → running → complete | error | timeout | cancelled
+```
+
+- `delegation_id` must be stable across `sessions.md`, supervisor input, and any summary/index entry.
+- Create the delegation record before dispatch with `delegation_status: registered`.
+- Set `delegation_status: running` after the background task id is recorded.
+- Set one terminal status exactly once after `background_output` is retrieved.
+- Terminal status is immutable.
+- Store one canonical YAML record at `runs/{run-id}/delegations/{delegation_id}.yaml`. It must include `delegation_id`, expected/actual agent, phase, dispatch mode, `background_task_id`, `child_session_id` when available, lifecycle status, `background_output_retrieved`, `retrieved_at`, `artifact_path`, `delegation_result_path`, title, bounded summary, evidence paths, blocker, and next action.
+- `sessions.md` is an index only: each row links to that canonical record. The supervisor receives the canonical record path, never a chat-only reconstruction.
+
+## Session ledger structure
+
+Use this structure for `runs/{run-id}/sessions.md`:
+
+```markdown
+# Session: {run-id}
+Updated: {ISO timestamp}
+
+## Goal
+{One sentence success criterion}
+
+## Confirmed Inputs
+- Workflow workspace:
+- Execution model: dual-container
+- Execution order: sequential
+- Baseline container set:
+- Optimized container set:
+- Baseline source root:
+- Optimized source root:
+- Topology target:
+- NPU devices / card count:
+- Model:
+- Train dataset:
+- Eval/test dataset:
+- Steps:
+- Batch size:
+- TP:
+- Metrics:
+
+## Current Phase
+- State: pending | ready | running | supervision | passed | failed | blocked
+- Active phase:
+- Current topology: single-node | dual-node | multi-node | custom | none
+- Next controller action:
+
+## Topology Pair Progress
+| Topology | Baseline | Optimized | Comparison | Supervisor | Next |
+|---|---|---|---|---|---|
+
+## Delegations
+| Delegation | Expected agent | Background task | Lifecycle | Retrieved at | Delegation record | Primary artifact | Summary |
+|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|
+
+## Latest Verdict
+- Supervisor verdict:
+- Blocker:
+- Next action:
+```
+
+Do not paste raw logs, full tracebacks, or dense output into `sessions.md`.
+
+### Runner failures
+
+```text
+baseline-runner failure
+→ baseline-preflight-repair reads evidence, diagnoses, repairs, returns retry-ready launch contract
+→ baseline-runner retries from the new launch contract
+→ workflow-supervisor closes the attempt outcome
+
+optimized-runner failure
+→ optimized-preflight-repair reads evidence, diagnoses, repairs, returns retry-ready launch contract
+→ optimized-runner retries from the new launch contract
+→ workflow-supervisor closes the attempt outcome
+```
+
+### Non-runner failures
+
+```text
+benchmark-comparator / experiment-reporter / workflow-supervisor failure
+→ debug-isolator
+→ workflow-supervisor
+→ retry the original failed phase
+```
+
+### Repair-attempt closure
+
+Use `runs/{run-id}/repair/{phase}/{topology}/index.yaml` as the append-only history for failed phase episodes. The debug/repair agent reads this index before proposing a new fix.
+
+```text
+runner failure
+→ preflight-repair reads index.yaml + original evidence paths
+→ preflight-repair writes attempts/attempt-N.yaml with status repair_ready
+→ runner re-runs using that attempt id
+→ runner writes only training facts and the new result path
+→ workflow-supervisor appends effective | ineffective | inconclusive
+→ next preflight-repair reads the index before proposing another fix
+```
+
+Rules:
+
+- `repair_ready` means only that the repair can be tested; it is not a claim that training is fixed.
+- Only a successful runner retry can establish `effective`.
+- A `fix_fingerprint` previously marked `ineffective` must not be proposed unchanged unless new evidence explains the material difference.
+- Runner retry results are written to append-only paths and never overwrite prior results.
+- `max_attempts` is recorded in the index and enforced by `workflow-supervisor` before approving another retry.
+
+## Required run state files
+
+```text
+runs/{run-id}/
+├── sessions.md
+├── intake/work-order.md
+├── delegations/{delegation-id}.yaml
+├── containers/baseline.yaml
+├── containers/optimized.yaml
+├── transitions/{topology}/baseline-to-optimized.yaml
+├── baseline/{topology}/result.yaml
+├── optimized/{topology}/result.yaml
+├── comparison/{topology}/result.yaml
+└── repair/{phase}/{topology}/
+    ├── index.yaml
+    └── attempts/attempt-N.yaml
+```
+
+## Controller loop
+
+1. Confirm required inputs and write `intake/work-order.md`.
+2. For each topology unit:
+   - Dispatch `baseline-runner` attempt 0 directly from the work-order, then dispatch `workflow-supervisor`.
+   - If baseline is blocked/failed/timed out, dispatch `baseline-preflight-repair`, supervise its retry contract, and retry `baseline-runner`.
+   - After baseline succeeds, require `transitions/{topology}/baseline-to-optimized.yaml` to prove workflow-owned Ray/process/port/NPU cleanup before optimized starts. If cleanup is unproven, the runner result is `blocked` and routes to `baseline-preflight-repair`.
+   - Dispatch `optimized-runner` attempt 0 directly from the work-order, then dispatch `workflow-supervisor`.
+   - If optimized is blocked/failed/timed out, dispatch `optimized-preflight-repair`, supervise its retry contract, and retry `optimized-runner`.
+   - Dispatch `benchmark-comparator` only after both runs succeed and optimized post-run cleanup is proven by its cleanup artifact.
+3. Never use gitworktree switching as a phase transition or recovery mechanism. On runner failure, repair only the assigned role container and its container-local runtime source.
+4. On non-runner failure, route to `debug-isolator`.
+5. After all topologies, dispatch `experiment-reporter` and then summarize approved artifacts to the user.
+
+## Verified RCA archive gate
+
+Any subagent that identifies a verified root cause and fix must complete an Experience Vault archive review before the controller continues. The controller must not advance when `archive_gate.archive_review_done` is missing or false.
+
+## Session ledger
+
+Maintain `runs/{run-id}/sessions.md` with confirmed inputs, current phase, topology progress, delegations, and latest supervisor verdict. Do not paste raw logs, full tracebacks, or dense output into `sessions.md`.
